---
// ProblemSection — "the problem" 3-card grid
---

<section class="problem">
  <div class="container">
    <p class="section-label reveal">The problem</p>
    <h2 class="section-title reveal">
      Software change needs a<br/>contract layer.
    </h2>
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0s">
        <div class="problem-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="28" height="28" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <path d="M14 2H6a2 2 0 00-2 2v16a2 2 0 002 2h12a2 2 0 002-2V8z"/>
            <path d="M14 2v6h6"/>
            <line x1="9" y1="15" x2="15" y2="15" opacity="0.5"/>
            <line x1="4" y1="12" x2="20" y2="12" stroke="#c9a55c" stroke-dasharray="2 3" opacity="0.6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Specs drift outside the repo</h3>
        <p>Requirements in wikis and tickets stop being enforceable the moment code moves. If the spec is not versioned and checked with the code, drift becomes invisible.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.1s">
        <div class="problem-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="28" height="28" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/>
            <path d="M7 8h10M7 12h6M7 16h8" opacity="0.5"/>
            <circle cx="18" cy="18" r="4" fill="none" stroke="#c9a55c" opacity="0.6"/>
            <path d="M18 16v4M16 18h4" stroke="#c9a55c" opacity="0.6" stroke-width="1.2"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Specs are invisible until something breaks</h3>
        <p>Plain-text specs give no feedback. You don't see what's verified, what's stale, or what's missing until a bug reveals it. There's no status at a glance.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="problem-card reveal" style="--reveal-delay: 0.2s">
        <div class="problem-icon">
          <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" width="28" height="28" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round">
            <rect x="3" y="3" width="18" height="18" rx="2"/>
            <path d="M7 8h4M7 12h8M7 16h6" opacity="0.5"/>
            <circle cx="17" cy="17" r="3" stroke="#c9a55c" opacity="0.6"/>
            <path d="M17 15.5v3M15.5 17h3" stroke="#c9a55c" opacity="0.6"/>
          </svg>
        </div>
        <h3>Agents need machine-readable contracts</h3>
        <p>AI coding workflows move quickly, but prompts are not a control plane. Agents need structured scope, explicit criteria, and a way to check what changed.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .problem {
    padding: 8rem 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }
  .problem-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 3rem;
  }
  .problem-card {
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    transition: border-color 0.3s, background 0.3s;
  }
  .problem-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--border-hover);
    background: var(--bg-card-hover);
  }
  .problem-icon {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }
  .problem-icon svg { display: inline-block; }
  .problem-card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }
  .problem-card p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
  }

  /* Light theme overrides */
  :global([data-theme='light']) .problem-icon svg line[stroke="#c9a55c"],
  :global([data-theme='light']) .problem-icon svg path[stroke="#c9a55c"],
  :global([data-theme='light']) .problem-icon svg circle[stroke="#c9a55c"] {
    stroke: #8a6c2f;
  }
</style>
